most_recent.text: I give them three stars as in neutral. I got green, pink, yellow/white and tan. They all measure and fit the same. I find this is uncommon for this brand in tees, tanks and other items. The fabric and weight of the skirts are quite heavy. They would slide down if you need them to fit in a very specific spot unless the tie is enough for the weight for your body type. The elastic waists are thick and super stretchy but not enough to pull up without unbuttoning them due to the zero stretch of the fabric. The colors are very true to the images on the listings. At 5'6" they all hit below knee but not quite mid calf. The first layer, pleated area hits me right at my thighs and I do not like the emphasis it puts on my body type. Also, given that it does have a tie and ruffle (potatoes sack style) at the top of the waistband, I think it is too much thickness and gawddy at the waist. Not a look I prefer either. The fabric is rough, not soft. I do not know how they will wash, if they'll shrink, wrinkle a lot (seems like it) or soften up. I also think it runs a bit bigger more than true to size. Some ladies pull these off well in the images, I hoped I could. No way, this neutral 3 stars.
most_recent.title: Good for some, not good for some
